<h4>[ext[Ethereum|https://ethereum.org]]</h4>

> Ethereum is a decentralized, open source, and distributed computing platform that enables the creation of smart contracts and decentralized applications, also known as [ext[Ðapp|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decentralized_application]].
>> <cite>[ext[consensys.net|https://consensys.net/knowledge-base/about-ethereum-eth/]]</cite>

<p>
  <b>IPFS with ~TiddlyWiki</b> uses the [ext[Ethereum blockchain|https://ethereum.org/en/developers/docs/intro-to-ethereum/]]
  as its identification, cryptographic and naming system layer.
</p>

<h4>[ext[ENS|https://ens.domains]]</h4>

> The [ext[Ethereum Name Service (ENS)|https://ens.domains]] is a distributed, open, and extensible naming system based on the Ethereum blockchain. ENS’s job is to map human-readable names like ‘alice.eth’ to machine-readable identifiers such as Ethereum addresses, other cryptocurrency addresses, content hashes, and metadata. ENS also supports ‘reverse resolution’, making it possible to associate metadata such as canonical names or interface descriptions with Ethereum addresses.
>> <cite>[ext[ens.domains|https://docs.ens.domains]]</cite>

<p>
  <b>IPFS with ~TiddlyWiki</b> uses [ext[ENS|https://app.ens.domains]] as its human readable naming system.
</p>

<h4>[ext[TiddlyWiki|https://tiddywiki.com]]</h4>

> ~TiddlyWiki is a personal wiki and a non-linear notebook for organising and sharing complex information. It is an open-source single page application wiki in the form of a single HTML file that includes CSS, ~JavaScript, and the content. It is designed to be easy to customize and re-shape depending on application. It facilitates re-use of content by dividing it into small pieces called Tiddlers.
>> <cite>[ext[wikipedia.org|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TiddlyWiki]]</cite>

<h3>IPFS with ~TiddlyWiki</h3>

<h3>Features</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Store ~TiddlyWiki's and attachments on [ext[IPFS|https://ipfs.io]]</li>
  <li>Access ~TiddlyWiki's and attachments from [ext[IPFS|https://ipfs.io]]</li>
  <li>Compress ~TiddlyWiki's and attachments</li>
  <li>Encrypt, Decrypt and Sign ~TiddlyWiki's and attachments
    <ul>
      <li>Standford</li>
      <li>Ethereum</li>
      <li>[ext[SHA-3|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA-3]]</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Import and Export</li>
  <li>Publish and Manage IPNS Keys and IPNS cids</li>
  <li>Interact with [ext[Metamask|https://metamask.io]] Ethereum wallets</li>
  <li>Publish to [ext[ENS|https://ens.domains]]</li>
  <li>Share over [ext[IPFS|https://ipfs.io]] ~TiddlyWiki's [ext[Tiddlers|https://tiddlywiki.com/#Tiddlers]] and attachments</li>
</ul>
